cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically 3D shape and viewpoint estimation from single images for robotics applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics applications, which suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper uses a convolutional neural network, which is a machine learning technique, indicating the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves self-supervision, which is a form of unsupervised learning, suggesting the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with grasping real-world objects, which is a task related to robotics and manipulation, indicating the category cs.GR (Graphics).
